        74.67079162597656,
        321.3076171875,
        87.15617370605469
      ],
      "text": "Analysis of CPI and WPI for the month of May, 2026 \n",
      "type": "text",
      "source_type": "pdfblock"
    },
    {
      "block_index": 4,
      "page": 15,
      "bbox": [
        79.08000183105469,
        99.03079223632812,
        81.89964294433594,
        111.51617431640625
      ],
      "text": " \n",
      "type": "empty",
      "source_type": "pdfblock"
    },
    {
      "block_index": 5,
      "page": 15,
      "bbox": [
        62.159996032714844,
        123.23289489746094,
        382.72509765625,
        135.8761749267578
      ],
      "text": "1. Inflation Scenario for the Month of May, 2026 (based on WPI) \n",
      "type": "text",
      "source_type": "pdfblock"
    },
    {
      "block_index": 6,
      "page": 15,
      "bbox": [
        79.08000183105469,
        147.27078247070312,
        553.6517944335938,
        174.8761749267578
      ],
      "text": "The annual rate of inflation based on All India Wholesale Price Index (WPI) number is 9.68% \n(provisional) for the month of May, 2026 (over May, 2025). \n",
      "type": "text",
      "source_type": "pdfblock"
    },
    {
      "block_index": 7,
      "page": 15,
      "bbox": [
        62.159996032714844,
        186.83290100097656,
        266.97955322265625,
        199.47618103027344
      ],
      "text": "2. WPI FOOD INDEX (Weight 24.99%)  \n",
      "type": "text",
      "source_type": "pdfblock"
    },
    {
      "block_index": 8,
      "page": 15,
      "bbox": [
        79.08000183105469,
        210.9907989501953,
        553.7384643554688,
        253.35617065429688
      ],
      "text": "The Food Index consists of \u2018Food Articles\u2019 from Primary Articles major group, and \u2018Manufacture of \nFood Products\u2019 from Manufactured Products major group. It observed a YoY inflation of 4.49 per cent \nin May 2026, compared to 3.11 per cent in April 2026. \n",
      "type": "text",
      "source_type": "pdfblock"
    },
    {
      "block_index": 9,
      "page": 15,
      "bbox": [
        62.159996032714844,
        265.432861328125,
        553.7053833007812,
        352.4761657714844
      ],
      "text": "3. Inflation Scenario for the Month of May, 2026 (based on CPI) \n \nThe Consumer Price Index (CPI: Base Year 2024) based inflation rate has increased to 3.93% \n(provisional) in May, 2026 from 3.48% in April, 2026. Consumer Food Price Index (CFPI) based \ninflation rate for All-India Combined has increased to 4.78% (provisional) in May, 2026 from 4.20% in \nApril, 2026. \n",
      "type": "text",
      "source_type": "pdfblock"
    },
    {
      "block_index": 10,
      "page": 15,
      "bbox": [
        62.159996032714844,
        364.6728820800781,
        384.18670654296875,
        377.316162109375
      ],
      "text": "4. A comparative study between the WPI and CPI inflation rates  \n",
      "type": "text",
      "source_type": "pdfblock"
    },
    {
      "block_index": 11,
      "page": 15,
      "bbox": [
        79.08000183105469,
        388.5908203125,
        553.5947265625,
        431.1961669921875
      ],
      "text": "WPI (Base Year 2022-23) based inflation rate increased by 1.42% (from 8.26% in April, 2026 to 9.68% \nin May, 2026) and CPI based inflation rate increased by 0.45 (from 3.48% in April, 2026 to 3.93% in \nMay, 2026).   \n",
      "type": "text",
      "source_type": "pdfblock"
    },
    {
      "block_index": 12,
      "page": 15,
      "bbox": [
        79.08000183105469,
        442.830810546875,
        553.7034912109375,
        500.316162109375
      ],
      "text": "The WPI (Base Year 2022-23) inflation for May, 2026 at 9.68% which is higher by 9.88% from the \nsame period last year (i.e. May, 2025 at -0.20%) and the CPI (Base Year 2024) inflation for May, 2026 \nis at 3.93% while CPI (Base Year 2012) inflation for the same period last year in May, 2025 was at \n2.82%.  \n",
      "type": "text",
      "source_type": "pdfblock"
    },
    {
      "block_index": 13,
      "page": 15,
      "bbox": [
        79.08000183105469,
        512.07080078125,
        553.6871948242188,
        569.4361572265625
      ],
      "text": "On the other hand, WPI (Base Year 2022-23) based Food Index inflation rate for May, 2026 at \n4.49% which is higher than the same period last year (i.e. May, 2025 at 0.09%) and the Consumer Food \nPrice Index (Base Year 2024) inflation rate for May, 2026 is at 4.78% while Consumer Food Price \nIndex (Base Year 2012) inflation rate for the same period last year in May, 2025 was at 0.99%. \n",
      "type": "text",
      "source_type": "pdfblock"
    },
    {
      "block_index": 14,
      "page": 15,
      "bbox": [
